{"type":"message","id":"24851160","parentId":"f30dea48","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:17:18.786Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. So:\n1. The entire workspace IS a git repo (v4-ecosystem-review)\n2. maiy-tech-hub is a subdirectory, not a separate git repo\n3. All the workspace files got mixed into the maiy-hub remote commits\n\nFor the maiy-hub project, I need to use a different approach. Since it's in a subdirectory of the workspace git repo, I have two options:\n\nOption A: Keep maiy-tech-hub as a subdirectory and just manage it carefully with git subtree or git filter-branch\nOption B: Create a separate git repo for maiy-tech-hub only\n\nActually, the cleanest solution for the Lead:1. maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub repo should ONLY contain the MAIY Tech Hub project files2. \n\nThe workspace files (agent configs, etc.) shouldn't be in that repo. The real issue is that my working directory was /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ - a monorepo for 34 agents. When I ran git commands, they applied to the whole workspace. To push just maiy-tech-hub to maiy-hub, I should use git subtree or a git archive approach, but the simplest solution is to keep them as separate repos entirely—v4-ecosystem-review for the agents and maiy-hub for the MAIY Tech Hub project itself.\n\nI can initialize a fresh git repo directly inside maiy-tech-hub as an independent project rather than a subdirectory of the workspace git repo.","thinkingSignature":"105f0e1f81d331389879b6b75b97863ed0a1442026a57800a45c72627a2d350b"},{"type":"text","text":"Sao mình lại thấy workspace V4 là git repo gốc — toàn bộ workspace bị lẫn vào nhau. Mình cần tách riêng:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_srrppy8prhlr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# maiy-tech-hub cần tách hoàn toàn khỏi workspace git\ncd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub\nrm -rf .git\ngit init\ngit remote add origin git@gitlab.com:maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub.git\ng